===subject:slavery vs resolution
===from:Kimberly Houston
===date:Fri Feb 14 23:35:07 2003
===message:To think that two groups that shared different veiws of this magnitude could resolve their various issues seems a bit impossible.  Both sides had their own views of the situations and had their reasonings as to why they felt the way they did.  Slavery in a nut shell was bad for all those involved.  It tarnished the lives of all involved, inclusing those against slavery.  Imagine living daily with a cause to abolish slavery and hundreds or thousands of people are against you?  Both sides had suffer, though the slaves suffered more.  I think there would be a big difference in our lives today if slavery had not been abolished.  None of our lives would be the same and many of us probably would not be here!
=========yorg=========
