===subject:HIST2110
===from:Linda Dawson
===date:Sun Feb 16 18:51:40 2003
===message:Yes, both were right because the issue of slavery would have continued to haunt the country and cause further seperation. No, a peaceful nonpartisan solution would have not been possible because there would have been further uprisings. Yes, a policy of moderation was doomed to fail because the Northerners wanted slavery to end immediately whereas the Southerners wanted slavery to continue indefinately. If the country were ran by moderates, slavery could have continued well into the 19th century, and the fanatics almost immediately ended a very blemished era in American history.
